item.title: A-Squared
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: This DJ duo are out to entertain the masses and spread good time through their sound. Not limiting themselves to one specific dance genre, A-Squared ever-changing style have helped them become party favourites in Cairo's house scene.

item.title: 47 Soul
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: 47SOUL is an Electro Arabic Dabke (Shamstep) band formed in Amman Jordan in 2013. The members are rooted in Bilad Al-Sham, spanning the divides from Amman to the Galilee to Ramallah and the rest of the Palestinian Diaspora. This new sound of 47SOUL has rapidly amassed fans in the Arab World and Europe by blasting the electric Arabic Dabke sound through underground music scenes. On top of the beats that have been bumping in the Arab World for centuries, 47SOUL hypes it up with analog synthesizers, hypnotic guitar lines, and shattering verses from the four singers.

item.title: Hany Must
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Hany Mustafa or Hany Must, is a singer/songwriter and musician who's sound borrows elements from the indie/acoustic to alternative & ambient music.

item.title: Glass Onion
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Egypt’s ultimate tribute band to The Beatles made up of respected solo musicians and dedicated fans. Four fab guys playing everything from Hamburg to Abbey Road.

item.title: H.O.H.
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Hany Adel (Wust El Balad), Ousso Lotfy (Nagham Masry) and Hany El Dakkak (Massar Egbari) join together and unite their best work into unplugged acoustic renditions of their much loved songs.

item.title: Sahra Band
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Sahra Band are one of the very few bands who perform Rai and fusion music in Egypt delivering a range of sounds that much like the desert, is wild yet warm; vast yet simple.

item.title: Massar Egbari
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Internationally acclaimed independent music sensations, Massar Egbari, meaning "Compulsory Detour" present rock, jazz, alternative Arabic and blues mixed with oriental music and powerful Egyptian lyrics discussing the social/ political issues the everyday person in Egyptian society faces.

item.title: Special K
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Mixing music to a thirsty Alexandria is how Mohamed Kamal started his career a long time ago. After taking time off, he now plays frequently on Friday nights at CJC, offering the crowd upbeat tech and deep house sets.

item.title: SHIHA
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: With more than 12 years of music production and DJing experience, SHIHA's work includes a variety of different projects including being the co-founder of Epic 101 Studios. He is known for his melodic deep house, tech, and progressive vibes.

item.title: FairouzT
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: FairouzT is a rising Egyptian female DJ. Born in Cairo with a natural passion for music. Known as the female sensation of Vocal House and Nu Disco.

item.title: Horrible DJs
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Timmy and Wally Mowafi make up the terribly entertaining duo Horrible DJs. With a satirical take on spinning music, these guys know how to pull a crowd and start a party.

item.title: The Cadillacs
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: With the taste of the 50s & the 80s Rockabilly Music, four Guys decided to spread their inspiration for this type of music to revive the Rockabilly and the Rock & Roll music in Egypt and the middle east.

item.title: Hisham Zahran
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: With a focus on deep, melodic and ethereal dance music, Hisham Zahran has steadily gained recognition within the dance music community thanks to his wildly popular online mixes.

item.title: Hend El Rawy
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Being a musician from an early age, Hend is no stranger to a variety of genres and doesn’t shy away from the idea of mixing and creating fusions using her upbringing within traditional Egyptian folk and exposure to modern Western sounds, be it electronic or rock music.

item.title: Sahra Band
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Sahra Band are one of the very few bands who perform Rai and fusion music in Egypt delivering a range of sounds that much like the desert, is wild yet warm; vast yet simple.

item.title: Wust El Balad
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: An amazing blend of sounds, combining traditional Arabic music with a modern and western twist, is successful in making their music as accessible as possible, not just in Cairo, but beyond. Wust El Balad deliver their pop-rock songs, addressing social issues paired with catchy lyrics and subtle Arabic

item.title: Sharmoofers
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: The Reggae-infused Arabic rock band Sharmoofers know how to amuse a crowd. Usually full of social commentary their lyrics touch their fans in a most relatable way.

item.title: Massar Egbari
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Internationally acclaimed independent music sensations, Massar Egbari, meaning "Compulsory Detour" present rock, jazz, alternative Arabic and blues mixed with oriental music and powerful Egyptian lyrics discussing the social/ political issues the everyday person in Egyptian society faces.

item.title: Ramy DJunkie
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: CJC regular Ramy DJunkie is one of our most sought after Spinning Wednesday DJs! Playing at CJC twice a month, Ramy spins everything from pop to disco to nostalgic Arabic pop, it just depends what night you catch him on! Whatever the music genre, Ramy DJunkie knows how to pull a crowd and start a crazy dance party.

item.title: Safi
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Safi is an Egyptian Radio and club DJ who is as versatile as he is focused. He plays everything from funk, to world music, to pop, to electronica. That extra special Safi touch though is house music infused with a touch of Arabic sounds, or as some might call it-Oriental Electronica. Safi is very active in Egypt and plays at least a gig a week. You can find him at CJC spinning away on our Spinning Wednesday nights.

item.title: Yehya Khalil
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Egypt’s jazz pioneer Yehya Khalil has been an active musician since the 60’s and has accomplished many great achievements in the local and international jazz music scene ever since. His unique compositions blend powerful percussive arrangements and authentic Eastern sounds with infectious jazz, offering an incredible musical journey.

item.title: Gawdat
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Dynamic DJ duo and siblings Gawdat joined the Student DJ Program back in 2013 and their DJ career has taken off ever since. Now, people wait in anticipation for the next time they get to hear the duo spin their infamous deep and tech house sets.

item.title: Mohasseb
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: CJC's monthly resident, DJ Mohasseb, is the epitome of progressive house in Egypt. Having only jump started his on deck career in 2011, he has already headlined Pacha Sharm El Sheikh’s New Year’s extravaganza two years in a row and become one of Egypt’s most sought after party machine.

item.title: Sorour
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Named after the band's lead singer, Sorour is distinguishable by Mohamed Sorour's resonant voice and the sound of traditional Arabic folk music fused with influences from around the world, including jazz, rock, and alternative music.

item.title: Hawas
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Hawas is an independent Egyptian band that presents alternative music that aims at exploring new musical dimensions through mixing different genres. They define their unique sound as Neo-Egyptian Pop.

item.title: Khayal
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: As the name suggests, this creative six piece Egyptian rock band Khayal exists because of the collective imagination of the band, who aim to give us an abstract look into their world.

item.title: Adam Clark Miller
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Singer, composer and songwriter, Adam Clark Miller has entertained audiences as a solo artist with various musicians and bands in the USA and now in Egypt for more than two decades. With a repertoire of music encompassing the entire history of Jazz and over two decades of performing under his belt, Adam has mastered modern vocal jazz.

item.title: Basheer
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Originating from Aswan Upper Egypt, Mohamed Basheer utilizes his deep cultural heritage of Ja’ffary culture and arts in creating a brilliant concoction of oriental sounds with modern fusions. Listening to his music will connect you to a different time, and to the unique Nubian culture.

item.title: Shereen Abdo
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Talented vocalist Shereen Abdo derives her inspiration from a vision that is simultaneously conservative regarding traditional folk and yet able to embrace diverse and progressive ways of producing sound.

item.title: Aguizi & Fahim
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Youssef El-Aguizi and Yehia Fahim, better known as Aguizi & Fahim burst into the scene in 2013 after winning Electrum Record's Student DJ competition. Since then they have stepped up the DJ game in Egypt and released many original productions and mixes.

item.title: Burdizo
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Launched in 2016, Burdizo is a new dance floor electro music project led by established electronic artist Mohamed Ragab.

item.title: Screwdriver
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: One of Egypt's most famous cover bands. Screwdriver has been active for over 15 years covering a wide range of music genres from 70's funk to today's top chart pop hits.

item.title: Malak El Husseiny
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Malak El Husseiny is a singer/songwriter from Cairo, Egypt. Malak’s voice, which has both softness and edge, is presented through electronic elements with a live earthy component. Incorporating Arabic lyrics with indie Western instrumentation.

item.title: Disco Misr
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Disco Misr is a young duo who have decided to revive Arabic pop and breathe new life into it by turning it into dancey party anthems with a twist of disco and funk.

item.title: Ahmed Saleh & Abdullah Miniawy
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Ahmed Saleh and Abdullah Miniawy join together for this special project that combines electronic experimental sounds from Saleh with controversial lyrics and enchanting Sufi singing by Miniawy.

item.title: Telepoetic
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Known for their experimental, raw and post-rock sound blending acoustic and electronics, Alexandrian trio Telepoetic form unique improvised melodies.

item.title: Aly B
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: DJ Aly B’s musical taste spans across a variety of genres from tech-house, nu-disco to 80’s pop. Nowadays he can be seen playing his crowd-drawing sets across Cairo nightclubs including CJC.

item.title: Mostafa Rizk
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Composer, singer and songwriter Mostafa Rizk may have uprooted from Aswan many years back, but has certainly kept his authentic Upper Egyptian charm thriving in all his music. Blending jazz and blues with an oriental twist, Mostafa has created his own unique sound.

item.title: Firehood
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Adham Roshdy's band Firehood for is for Hard Rock lovers, they very skillfully cover all your favorite classics from Aerosmith, Queen, AC/DC, and a whole lot more!

item.title: Dokkan
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Dokkan is a young & talented musical formation that plays contemporary instrumental music, mixed with more traditional Arabic sounds. Each band member has mastered their instrument to come together and produce beautifully melodic sounds. They accomplish this by playing oud, guitar, percussion, and upright bass.

item.title: Ahmed Safi
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Ahmed Safi is an Egyptian singer/songwriter. He aims to merge cultures by blending western influences such as indie, soul and jazz with traditional Egyptian musical influences. Other than his solo career, he is is a part of local band Sukoon.

item.title: DeeRailed
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: DeeRailed is an up-and-coming DJ in the house music scene and one of very few female DJs in Cairo! She has frequented our Friday nights more recently and is becoming known for her deep house melodic sets.

item.title: Special K
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Mixing music to a thirsty Alexandria is how Mohamed Kamal started his career a long time ago. After taking time off, he now plays frequently on Friday nights at CJC, offering the crowd upbeat tech and deep house sets.

item.title: Ouzo
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Influencing the DJ scene in Egypt since 2001, Ouzo was resident where most DJ's aspire to perform at; Pacha Sharm El Sheikh. Now based in Cairo and playing gigs regularly around the city, Ouzo is known for his distinctive style of uplifting tech house with a progressive edge.

item.title: SHIHA
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: With more than 12 years of music production and DJing experience, SHIHA's work includes a variety of different projects including being the co-founder of Epic 101 Studios. He is known for his melodic deep house, tech, and progressive vibes.

item.title: Richard R.
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: With over a decade of DJ'ing under his belt, Richard R. has become a popular name in the music scene in Cairo. His music is a mix of Deep House, Electronica and Techno.

item.title: Zahed Sultan
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Zahed Sultan is a Kuwait-based alternative electronic music and multimedia artist. Creating an audio-visual experience for his audience, he believes and aims for his performances to be interactive; a collaboration between himself and the audience. Zahed's music plays both with lyrics and the interesting and intricate electronic sounds.

item.title: FairouzT
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: FairouzT is a rising Egyptian female DJ. Born in Cairo with a natural passion for music. Known as the female sensation of Vocal House and Nu Disco.

item.title: The Meteors Project
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Inspired by everything between early prog-rock, trip hop and amalgamations of neo-classical and techno, The Meteors Project is a reflection of existential themes and questions. Creating movement through solid grooves supplemented by complex layers of polyphony and harmony, every installment is an exploration of oneself and its relationship to the big blue ball floating in the sky.

item.title: Gurumiran
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Gurumiran is an audiophile, DJ, audio engineer, guitarist, lyricist, music producer and songwriter based in Beirut, Lebanon.

item.title: Omar Sherif
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded:
Uplifting, emotional and driving would best describe Omar Sherif's sound. He brings progressive house melodies to CJC's decks but takes it up a BPM or two when producing his internationally acclaim Trance tracks.
DJ & producing with FSOE (Future Sounds Of Egypt) Recordings, Omar has also released his productions on various labels including Armada & Subculture supported by Aly & Fila, Armin Van Buuren, JOC & many more.

item.title: SHawky
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: One of the our most versatile DJ's, SHawky reinvents himself yet again, crossing over in to tech house territory with a fine selection of melodic house tunes, mixed with rugged bass lines and pumping beats.

item.title: Funk Off
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: A high-energy band that covers all of your favorite hits from different genres such as funk, disco, blues, rock and pop.

item.title: Islam Chipsy
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Exploding out of Cairo, Egypt, Islam chipsy and his band E.E.K. are a force of nature described by those who've been caught in the eye of their storm as one of the most exciting live performances around. At the core of E.E.K lies electro shaabi keyboard pioneer Islam Chipsy, whose joyous, freewheeling sonic blitz warps the standard oriental scale system into otherworldly shapes, joined by Islam Ta’ta’ and Khaled Mando raining down a percussive storm behind dual drum kits. With a trail of international club and festival shows in the past year, they have cemented their word-of-mouth reputation as a must-see live act.

item.title: Voice & Bass
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Amy Frega’s vocals and Samer George on bass cover all time hits as well as original music from Samer George’s new album “All you Need is Bass".

item.title: The Cadillacs
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: With the taste of the 50s & the 80s Rockabilly Music, four Guys decided to spread their inspiration for this type of music to revive the Rockabilly and the Rock & Roll music in Egypt and the middle east.

item.title: Bluezophrenia
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Born into Cairo's live music scene in 2013, this young spirited blues and rock n' roll band don't just sound the part, they play, move and dress the part too. Performing popular covers and Bluezophrenia originals.

item.title: A.K.
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: A.K reinvents himself on Cairo Jazz Club's decks time and time again bringing the freshest RnB and Hip Hop themes to Cairo's urban crowds. 'Straight Outta Cairo', 'Bigger Better Louder' and the newest theme 'Let Loose' have become staples of CJC's Spinning Wednesday events.

item.title: Hisham Zahran
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: With a focus on deep, melodic and ethereal dance music, Hisham Zahran has steadily gained recognition within the dance music community thanks to his wildly popular online mixes.

item.title: Cairo Bigband Society
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: The first in its kind in Cairo since the 70's, The Big Band Society are an Egyptian medley of 15+ of the finest jazz musicians in town. Led by renowned jazz pianist Hesham Galal, and everyone's favourite voice, Amr Yehia on vocals.

item.title: Cocoon
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Led by Hesham Galal on piano, Cocoon are the liveliest Latin and Cuban jazz formation in Cairo.

item.title: Ahmed Omar 'Africairo'
item.dc:creator: Dev

item.title: Abou Samra
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Abou Samra discovered his love of music very early on, and by the age of 13 he had his first pioneer mixer and 2 vinyls. Things snowballed from there and he soon developed himself in the underground scenes of Cairo and Barcelona. Leaving Egypt for two years to pursue his passion for music; now he's back with entertainment brand Blurr to teach the dance scene a thing or two about how tech house and techno should be done.

item.title: Eslam El Sha'ary
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Eslam El Sha'ary and his exquisite spiritual fusion ensemble perform central Asian flavored music and flaunts Eslam's rare instruments; Afghan Rabab, Persian Tar and the Dukduk.

item.title: Feedo
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Famous for the juiciest Hip Hop and RnB master mixes on his weekly prime time Nile FM show, ‘Friday Night Flavas’, DJ Feedo has been the go to person for Hip Hop, RnB and commercial hits in Egypt since 1997.

item.title: Nathalie Saba
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Bursting onto the urban pop scene in early 2015, signing with none other that Sony Music Entertainment Middle East, Nathalie redefines what is it to be a female pop artist in Egypt.

item.title: Shahira Kamal
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Shahira Kamal performs originals and cover songs with her band Shahira Kamal & The Band. She writes and sings her own original lyrics, and composes her own melodies. Her sound is acoustic, indie, and very distinct. Her voice is beautiful and homey, leaving you with an intense feeling of satisfaction.

item.title: Sync Tank
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Sync Tank is a live electronic duo from Cairo Egypt, featuring all original music.

item.title: Who Killed Bruce Lee
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Perhaps the name strikes one first, but as soon as these four bearded men hit the stage with their energetic set, the crowd does not seem to mind the confusion the name creates.

item.title: Hend El Rawy
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Being a musician from an early age, Hend is no stranger to a variety of genres and doesn’t shy away from the idea of mixing and creating fusions using her upbringing within traditional Egyptian folk and exposure to modern Western sounds, be it electronic or rock music.

item.title: Danny Malak
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Lebanese/Russian acoustic solo artist. Playing all your favorite rock and blues.

item.title: Almena
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Independent music project Almena established themselves foremost as an expressive music platform to enrich the live music scene in Alexandria. They heavily touch on the social and economic restraints with their sound, lyrics and blend of music genres from contemporary Arabic to blues, rock, reggae and jazz.

item.title: Storm Band
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Storm Band experiment with sounds of oriental music, reforming the old songs and reproducing the heritage of Oriental Music in a modern way.

item.title: MEM (Machine Eat Man)
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: The widely acclaimed electronic artist Mohamed Ragab, is an Egyptian musician, composer, producer and a synthesist, based in Cairo.

item.title: Baher
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Always in search for greater ends and different sounds, Baher has never limited himself to the rules of genres and styles. He is a devoted DJ who like to connect to people through his music. He specializes in tech house and techno.

item.title: Arthur Satyan
item.dc:creator: Dev

item.title: Sharmoofers
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: The Reggae-infused Arabic rock band Sharmoofers know how to amuse a crowd. Usually full of social commentary their lyrics touch their fans in a most relatable way.

item.title: Screwdriver
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: One of Egypt's most famous cover bands. Screwdriver has been active for over 15 years covering a wide range of music genres from 70's funk to today's top chart pop hits.

item.title: Ouzo
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: Influencing the DJ scene in Egypt since 2001, Ouzo was resident where most DJ's aspire to perform at; Pacha Sharm El Sheikh. Now based in Cairo and playing gigs regularly around the city, Ouzo is known for his distinctive style of uplifting tech house with a progressive edge.

wp:postmeta.wp:meta_value: The Embassy of Poland in Cairo in association with CJC bring you reggae from Poland! Siblings and DJ duo Gawdat started their career playing at underground and house parties, and now they pull a huge, energetic crowd wherever they play their tech and deep house sets! Join us for the first Manic Monday of the month, because these guys are sure to get the month off to a good start.

item.dc:creator: Dev

wp:postmeta.wp:meta_value:
Dina El Wedidi is an Egyptian new folk and fusion singer, composer and guitarist. She will be performing her original acoustic compositions, reflecting her thoughts on political and social issues with her expressive voice and engaging lyrics.

item.dc:creator: Dev

wp:postmeta.wp:meta_value: Safi and Ramy The #DJunkie are at it again with some Dirrrty POP! Prepare to get down and dirrrty to some of your favorite 90’s pop jams.

item.title: Gawdat / Mohasseb
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: G

wp:postmeta.wp:meta_value: We bring you a night of the most interesting electronic music that Egypt has to offer! Telepoetic will mesmerize you with their skilled and calculated use of instruments and synthesizers. Machine Eat Man will then continue this electronic journey and blow your mind with his unique Electronica sound.

DJ Feedo is back for another night of gettin’ down and breakin' it down at CJC! Putting the ‘hip’ in hip hop, Feedo will be playing a heavy dose of RnB and Hip Hop, spinning everything from old school to your favorite current hits!

It’s time for Thursday Night Live, which means a night for some great live music to kick off your weekend! Bluezophrenia will rock the house with their spot-on blues and rock n roll. Screwdriver Band skillfully cover all your favorite hits and ensure you don’t stop dancing as always.
DJ Fabric is back at CJC after a very long time! It's Friday Fever and you can depend on DJs Fabric and Special K get the weekend started on an upbeat note with their house sets!

For this week’s edition of Saturday L’Oriental, Storm Band takes traditional Egyptian songs and breathes new life into them, creating a connection to today’s Egyptian youth. Their unique sound will blow you away.
Sticking to the traditional, the upper Egyptian musician Basheer will sing his captivating folk music which is sure to take you to another time and place.

The 15+ man formation that is The Big Band Society elegantly plays jazz like you’ve never heard it before! To add some Latin flare to this jazzy evening, prepare to be dazzled by Cocoon BAND's Latin and Cuban jazz!

This week’s edition of #AltTuesday brings you a back-to-roots type of night.
Influenced by his versatile background, Ahmed omar uses the different cultures that shaped his identity as inspiration for his musical creativity and produces a delightful blend of African and Arabic music.
Between Asia Madani's unforgettable folky Sudanese vocals and the sound of her percussion, she provides a traditional yet unique sound.

Don't blame it on the sunshine Don't blame it on the moonlight Don't blame it on the good times Blame it on the BOOGIE!
Ramy The #DJunkie brings us another wild Boogie Night! Leave your worries at the door and prepare to dance the night away.

We bring you yet another Thursday Night Live with the best that the local live music scene has to offer! Singer and guitarist Danny Malak covers the best pop and rock hits with a soft acoustic spin.
Hassan Ramzy Band will be playing in their new, full-on band formation, where they will be performing exciting original alternative and indie rock songs.

One of the most popular and regular CJC DJ Mohasseb is back for yet another unforgettable night of your favorite progressive house tracks! These nights usually need no introduction because Mohasseb has long established himself as a party starter at CJC.

Alexandrian band Almena - الميناء will be joining us this Saturday, playing guitar-led contemporary Arabic music inspired by a variety of world music.
Also joining us on this Arabic musical evening is Hawas هوس, an independent Egyptian band that presents alternative music which aims at exploring new musical dimensions through mixing different genres. They define their unique sound as "Neo-Egyptian Pop."
Tech house experts Baher and Ouzo will be joining us this Monday for a night where you leave your worries at the door, and focus on your dancing and their kick-ass sets!

As the name suggests, Bluenotes are all about the blues! The band is a blues-rock formation that draws influences from several types of blues music. Expect growling vocals, a soulful harmonica, and screaming guitars!
Friday nights aren’t the same without great electronic music! Misty and hafez keep the crowd dancing all night long.
Get ready for a sophisticated evening as the charismatic Voice & Bass and Michelle Rounds will be singing some jazzy favorites.

Singer and guitarist Danny Malak, covers the best pop and rock hits with a soft acoustic spin. The Hassan Ramzy Band will be playing in their new, full-on band formation, where they will be performing exciting original alternative and indie rock songs.

These funky DJ's cover the dance music spectrum drawing from funk, disco, soul and everything in between! Other than playing thumping dance beats, these guys love to regularly feature artists to keep their sound exciting and fresh, and this time they’re bringing in none other than local music pioneer and renowned guitarist Ousso! This should be a show for the books, expect high energy and dancing till the wee hours of the morning!

item.title: Hend Al Rawy / The Meteors Project
item.dc:creator: Dev

wp:postmeta.wp:meta_value:
17- Hend El Rawy/ The Meteors project: We've got a very special Alt Tuesday for you this week! Playing with the traditional, the folk, the electronic and the experimental, we cross boundaries and blur musical lines all within a few hours and under one roof! We are extremely pleased to welcome the talented vocalist Hend El Rawy on our stage! Being a musician from an early age, Hend is no stranger to a variety of genres and doesn’t shy away from the idea of mixing and creating fusions using her upbringing within traditional Egyptian folk and exposure to modern Western sounds, be it electronic or rock music. Hend joined the French band Orange Blossom a few years back and toured all over Europe, offering their loyal fans a unique blend of folk music mixed with electronic sounds. Now Hend is back in Egypt and has formed her very own band! This new formation will be playing original folk-rock fusion songs as well as some songs from Orange Blossom this Tuesday. Don’t miss this unique display of local talent.
Inspired by everything between early prog-rock, trip hop and neo-classical and techno, The Meteors Project will play one of their captivating live electronic sets. Their new EP ‘Swimming with Astronauts’ is definitely worth checking out and will be even better live!

Named after the band's lead singer, Sorour is distinguishable by Mohamed Sorour's resonant voice and the sound of traditional Arabic folk music fused with influences from around the world.
Hawidro, meaning 'the return' in Nubian, take their audience back to Mother Africa with multiple influences from the region, which they combine with international sounds, making them the unique band that they are.
We are happy to host one of Egypt’s favorite and longest standing contemporary bands, Wust El Balad
Fun, Easy, upbeat and dancey! These are all things that you can expect on this night along with a heavy dose of nostalgia as you listen to some 90’s favorites!
This veteran DJ knows how to get a party started and keep the crowd moving all night long! Established both locally and abroad, Hisham Zahran is unarguably one of the best house DJ's in the scene.

A Squared celebrate their second anniversary at CJC! We’re proud to have had this duo play regularly on our decks over the past couple of years and we invite you to come cheers to many more years to come!

This Alt Tuesday celebrates local indie music! Singer/songwriter Ahmed Safi plays an acoustic set of his indie original songs from his band, Sukoon as well as some covers. Expect a delectable fusion of Eastern and jazzy sounds.

As intriguing as their name is, once you hear these guys play you’ll find their special electro-punk indie rock sound is even more intriguing! Not only will the Lebanese band be playing at CJC for the very first time, but this is also your last chance to catch them in the Middle East Region till October 2017!
Safi will make sure that the beginning and end of the night is just as delectable as the middle with his unique Oriental Electronica.

item.title: Sebzz / Shiha (B.day Bash)
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded: It’s Shiha’s birthday and he’s celebrating it at CJC! Join him in celebrating the way him and Sebzz know best; by spinning kick ass house sets all night long!

wp:postmeta.wp:meta_value: CJC regulars and one of Egypt’s most valued contemporary bands are back for another evening of great original music with their jazz and rock-infused Arabic melodies.
Indie artist and singer Shahira Kamal debuts at CJC, showing off her soft melodious voice and indie songs. The talented Shereen Abdo returns to our stage for a dose of her indie folk/rock music.
We are pleased to have Egyptian singer/songwriter Nathalie Saba debuting on our stage, where she’ll be playing pop covers as well her original songs.

Have we got a surprise for YOU! Let Loose is an all-new night where A.K. will be playing anything from Hip Hop to RnB, to Pop and all your favorite current jams! Let down your hair, leave your worries at the door, and expect the unexpected!

DJ Feedo is back for another night of gettin’ down and breakin' it down at CJC! Putting the ‘hip’ in hip hop, Feedo will be playing a heavy dose of RnB and Hip Hop, spinning everything from old school to your favorite current hits!
Amro and The Big Bang Boogie will provide you with some masterful Pop and Rock covers on this Thursday Night Live! Come ready to party and dance the night away!

item.title: Hassan El Far / Special K / Omar Sherif
item.dc:creator: Dev

wp:postmeta.wp:meta_value: It’s Hassan El Far's debut spinning solo! Being part of DJ trio FAM, we’re sure he’s got something great cooked up for us. Special K and Omar Sherif will then take over to keep you on your feet!

Basheer and his Upper Egyptian sound and soulful voice will be reviving folk music this Saturday L'Oriental! The talented musician will sing his captivating folk music which is sure to take you to another time and place.

Eslam El Sha'ary conquers this musically-rich evening with his own unique sound of world fusion music which includes an array of wonderfully mastered and intriguing instruments. El Sha’ary’s music is said to “give expression to his mystical experiences”.

item.title: Tech Tech Discotech ft. Hafez / Shady Ezz
item.dc:creator: Dev

wp:postmeta.wp:meta_value: A fun new night to move your feet to! Step into our dazzling tech dance haven, where Omar Hafez and Shady Ezz fanpage take us to new colourful highs. Expect a whole lotta energy and really great vibes. Due to the special happenings on this night, it's a guest list only event so hurry and get your names on the list.

item.title: Disco 7amra ft. Aguizi & Fahim / Disco Misr
item.dc:creator: Dev

wp:postmeta.wp:meta_value: Time for another Disco 7amra where we celebrate all things upbeat and of course some Oriental disco! This night is for our party people! Aguizi & Fahim will kick off the night with another great set, followed by Disco Misr who will be spinning some funky Oriental disco for the rest of the night.

Radio Acid is an experimental electronic music formation that serves up groovy beats, high voltage analogue synths, and spacey guitar sounds to take the audience to other dimensions! Known for their experimental, raw and post-rock sound blending acoustic and electronics, Alexandrian trio Telepoetic form unique, improvised melodies.

We bring you three kick-ass live electronic acts on a Thursday! We know you like to party hard on the weekend, so we thought why not bring an upbeat night to all the electronic music lovers out there! Finrod is a trio who attempt taking an altered direction in composing/writing music. They mix electronic keyboard sounds with ambient sounds and vocals and bass. This creates a unique sound that is both soothing and groovy.
Inspired by everything between early prog-rock, trip hop and neo-classical and techno, The Meteors Project will play one of their captivating live electronic sets. Their new EP ‘Swimming with Astronauts’ displays even further the scope of talent that this band has!
Electronic music producer NEOBYRD provides a one-of-a-kind live performance for his audience. He has received recognition across the Middle East for his musical achievements through awards and mentions.

Mohasseb is back at it again! These nights usually need no introduction because Mohasseb has long established himself as a party starter at CJC. As always, he’ll be playing your favorite progressive house tracks!

Founded almost two decades ago and one of the first Egyptian bands to deliver an original mixture of jazz and Arabic tunes and melodies, El Dor El Awal are sure to captivate your senses! Come listen and sway to their great instrumental jazzy music, we’re sure you won’t be able to resist.

A new direction for our Sunday nights with two of our most soulful acoustic artists, Danny Malak and Hassan Ramzy. Singer and guitarist Danny Malak performs the best pop and rock hits with a soft acoustic spin. Then Hassan Ramzy's soulful voice and melodious songs carry the rest of this rich night.

We are pleased to announce that Jimmy Gamal Adel will be debuting at CJC! Despite being fairly new to the scene, Jimmy has already displayed his talent abroad. Now we’re excited to share his great tech-house beats with you right here on our decks!
Siblings and DJ duo Gawdat started their career playing at underground and house parties, and now they pull a huge, energetic crowd wherever they play their tech and deep house sets! These guys are sure to supply you with just the right dose of house music to keep you moving all night long.

Being a musician from an early age, Hend el Rawy is no stranger to a variety of genres and doesn’t shy away from the idea of mixing and creating fusions using her upbringing within traditional Egyptian folk and exposure to modern Western sounds, be it electronic or rock music. Hend joined the French band Orange Blossom a few years back and toured all over Europe, offering their loyal fans a unique blend of folk music mixed with electronic sounds. Now Hend is back in Egypt and has formed her very own band! This new formation will be playing original folk-rock fusion songs as well as some songs from Orange Blossom this Tuesday. Don’t miss this unique display of local talent.

item.title: My Ugly Ex ft. Ramy DJunkie
item.dc:creator: sara

wp:postmeta.wp:meta_value:
Sick of dwelling over the past? Tired of seeing your ex at parties? Fed up of scrolling through their FB photos? Then dry your eyes and come boogie the night away and forget all about your ugly ex! Disclaimer: This ain’t no pity party, this is for the people who want to celebrate instead of mourn!
Happy (anti) Valentine’s day!

Singer/songwriter Shady Ahmed will be gracing us with his smooth voice, performing acoustic original and cover songs. Egypt’s ultimate tribute band to The Beatles, Glass Onion, is made up of respectable solo artists &musicians in their own rights as well as dedicated Beatles fans.
House experts Misty and Ouzo will be joining us this Friday for a night where you leave your worries at the door, and focus on your dancing and their kick-ass sets!

item.title: Electro Sha3bi ft. Islam Chipsy / El Sweasy & Alaa Fifty
item.dc:creator: sara

wp:postmeta.wp:meta_value: We’re doing it sha3bi style for this week’s edition of Saturday L’Oriental! Islam Chipsy, El Sweasy & Alaa 50 will play a music genre that we all know and love by now: Electro Sha3bi. Created not so long ago and nothing short of homegrown right here in Cairo, the heavily electronic musical style called Mahraganat is characterized by keyboards (in Chipsy’s case wild hands flying along the keyboard) mixed with more traditional “sha3bi” pop music.
This 15+ man formation plays jazz like you’ve never heard it before! To add some Latin flare to this jazzy evening, prepare to be dazzled by Cocoon BAND’s Latin and Cuban jazz!

Things are about to get super manic on Monday as not only do we have two of the best DJs in town, but we’re also bringing back The Lab! You know what that means, put on your lab coats and get ready to get experimental! Ladies & gentlemen, please welcome Gaser & Sebzz on our decks for this night of musical madness. Tech-nically speaking, this one's going to be off the hook.
One of Egypt’s favorite contemporary bands, Wust El Balad play original pop-rock songs with expressive lyrics.

item.title: Taxi El Sahra ft. Ramy DJunkie
item.dc:creator: sara

wp:postmeta.wp:meta_value: Good news folks, We have another Taxi El Sahra for you this month! You know the drill: get ready to time travel back to the 90’s as Ramy The #DJunkie lays down some serious Arabic and English Pop.

Egypt’s jazz pioneer Yehya Khalil & his Egyptian Jazz Fusion Band return to the CJC stage! His unique compositions blend powerful percussive arrangements & authentic Eastern sounds with infectious jazz, offering an incredible musical journey that nourishes both mind and soul.

Meshwar is an Arabic reggae band! That’s right! These “self-proclaimed musicians for peace” will take us on a laid-back ‘meshwar’ (journey) with their groovy Arabic reggae tunes! Hawas is an independent Egyptian band that presents alternative music which aims at exploring new musical dimensions through mixing different genres.

item.title: Nadah El Shazly / Karim El Ghazoly
item.dc:creator: sara

wp:postmeta.wp:meta_value:
We're happy to introduce a new improvisational trio featuring Nadah El Shazly (Vocals), Karim El Ghazoly (Drums & FX), and Cherif El-Masri (Synthesizer & FX). The group enjoys spontaneously creating surreal atmospherics, examining medical curiosities, and taking long walks on the beach.
Seriously though, this should be a very interesting experimental project that we're really looking forward to seeing! We're betting it can't go wrong having these three top-notch musicians working together...so come to CJC on Tuesday for an enchanting night of magical sounds!

item.title: Cairo-Jazz-Club
item.dc:creator: Dev

item.title: Nader Tahawy ft. Omar Sherif (Anniversary & Bday Bash)
item.dc:creator: sara

wp:postmeta.wp:meta_value: A double whammy of a party tonight as we celebrate Nader Tahawy’s CJC anniversary and BDAY! And what better way to have it large than by adding his DJ bestie, Omar Sherif to the decks. Don’t miss this epic gathering of friends, as we raise a glass to Tahawy on the dance-floor!

Mohasseb will be laying down the usual musical goodness, but with a little help from his friends! Joining him for this evening will be none other than Veteran DJ and crowd favorite Aly Goede. We can’t wait to see (and hear) what happens on this stylistically versatile evening!

We are proud to present to you Shereen Abdo's new jazz project; Jazzy Me! Shereen is well known in the indie scene for her oriental singing style, but the artist is continuously growing and becoming more versatile. In her new project, she will be performing her favorites -and yours-by Frank Sinatra, Billie Holiday, Ella Fitzgerald and Nina Simone among others. Jazzy Me is defined by Shereen’s powerful voice, paired with sounds of piano, bass and percussions- a performance which promises to take you back in time!

Indie artist and singer Shahira Kamal Music debuts at CJC, showing off her soft melodious voice and indie songs. The talented Shereen Abdo returns to our stage for a dose of her unique indie folk/rock music.

item.title: About CJC

item.content:encoded: [vc_row][vc_column][cjc_about_section title="About Cairo Jazz Club" img="358"]Laid back, hi-energy and fun. For well over a decade, Cairo Jazz Club has stood the test of time as Cairo’s ultimate live music hub. The vibe achieved in our venue is a lively and engaging one where people can enjoy live music, delicious food and bar selections, while feeling right at home. In the center of it all, the Cairo Jazz Club stage is notoriously established as a portal for manifesting art and expression through music. It has stood witness to the rise of many fresh talents, regularly hosting the finest live acts in town, as well as exciting international artists. We also make it our mission to tirelessly expose new talent and present them with the space and opportunity to grow; we have been the starting ground for countless artists in the independent music scene. Adamant on catering to all tastes while remaining musically objective, Cairo Jazz Club hosts a different event every day, covering various genres, in addition to the occasional themed nights. The philosophy that has kept us going thus far is simpler than you would think, “We serve good moods”. And that is precisely what is on the menu every day of the week. So if you enjoy having a good time while feeding your appetite with a delectable, diverse menu and euphorically intoxicating cocktails, then Cairo Jazz Club is the place to be.[/cjc_about_section][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][cjc_about_section title="STAGE HISTORY" img="359" direction="Left"]From the get go, a fundamental essential to the Cairo Jazz Club experience was its stage, instrumental in the evolution of Cairo’s independent music scene. Cairo Jazz Club has always platformed fresh talent leading to why most of the city’s top end bands such as Wust El Balad and Screwdriver were born on that stage. The stage until now is a regular host to the finest live acts in town and . The Club is rightly recognized as the “capital” of live music in the city. Some of the many musical talents who have taken to Cairo Jazz Club’s stage: Established Egyptian Artists Fathy Salama Yehya Khalil Rashad Fahim Ahmed Rabie Salah Ragab Ossama Ezz El Din Hesham Galal Internationally Acclaimed Artists Ilham Madfai Natasha Atlas Stanley Jordan Monica Passos Jay Rodriguez Michiel Bortslap Albert Del Rio Mark Alban Last Supper Band Los Banditos Band Ned Kelly Kamal Musallam Mashrou’ Leila Tania Saleh Souad Massi OUM Ghalia Ben Ali Zeid Hamdan Top Local Artists who debuted at CJC Wust EL Balad Beshir The Riff Band Screwdriver Eftekasat Vybe Cocoon Mica Cairo Bigband Society [/cjc_about_section][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][cjc_about_section title="CJC’s Art" img="361"] Cairo Jazz Club was very lucky to work with different creative artistic talents over the years. Known for our unique drawings, mystical interior design and authentic print work, CJC has to commend the imaginative minds of those who helped inspire our identity and character that followed. Amr Qenawi: Current Graphic Designer & Art Director                                                                                       Although his line of work requires versatility in style, CJC’s resident designer Amr Qenawi’s unique artistic identity is embedded in all aspect of his CJC designs. Creative flyers, posters, graphics and interior themed decoration all show the admirable objectivity in his work. Qenawi has recently taken on the task of art directing CJC’s themed nights, creating different moods using his creativity and props mostly worked on by hand. Upon graduating with a BA in applied arts in 2008, Amr launched his career as a painter and computer graphic artist. He draws inspiration from the likes of surrealist giant, H.R Giger; Spanish Fantasy Characters artist, Luis Royo; and the prince of darkness himself, Marilyn Manson. Amr is also one of the very few artists around that are willing to take on the tedious yet beautifully sophisticated art of Rotoscopy, completing Neobyrd’s entire music video ‘My Sweetheartless’ with a whopping 3800 individually coloured frames within months of filming.  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FP5ktZWketk Karine Ghaly: CJC Artist responsible for the unique illustrations If you ever wondered who was the creative mastermind behind the illustrations that inspired everything from our logo to our tables and façade, look no further than artist Karine Ghaly. Born in Alexandria Egypt, Karine graduated from the University of Fine Art Alexandria and went on to attend courses at St Martin’s College of art and design in London. Karine used her love of Egypt and of music to help influence the logo and illustrations for Cairo Jazz Club. By combining her creative imagination with a modern twist she was able to create a feel of freedom and relaxed environment matching CJC’s ambiance. Karine also acknowledges CJC’s owners for having a big impact on the creative process and final designs. Karine has had exhibitions at the Ostia Lido’s Art Gallery in Rome. Waterloo’s Art Gallery in Brussels, the Crédit Mutuel in France, Spanish Cultural Center, and various locations in Cairo such as International Cultural Center for Cooperation. Amr Farouk: Interior Paintings (CJC Agouza)  Bohemian artist and designer Amr Farouk is the craftsman behind the series of intriguing paintings hanging inside Cairo Jazz Club. Amr Farouk was a painter from his early days as a curious child. Born in Cairo, Amr moved to Sinai from the age of 15 and lived a Bedouin lifestyle over the following 22 years. Moving from one area to another, spending a lot of time in the mountains, Amr’s artistic talents developed at a rapid rate, excelling him to greater spiritual enlightenment. His travels and free living attitude is well represented in his art at Cairo Jazz Club. Mahmoud Fahmy: Graphic Designer  Cool and collected Egyptian freelance designer Mahmoud Fathy brought the CJC drawings to life in 2010 and was responsible for the first batch of CJC printed materials including the creative and upbeat series of posters and flyers CJC generated for bands and festivals. Mahmoud studied design at faculty of Fine Arts in Cairo and worked for numerous organizations such as Promo 7 and LOWE Egypt. He currently lives in Berlin and works for worldwide advertising agency DDB. http://www.mahmoud-fathy.com/[/cjc_about_section][/vc_column][/vc_row]

item.title: CJC Nights
item.dc:creator: Dev
item.content:encoded:
[vc_row][vc_column][cjc_night title="Jazz Sunday" img="8" embed="https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?visual=true&url=http%3A%2F%2Fapi.soundcloud.com%2Fusers%2F1819173&show_artwork=true&maxwidth=270&maxheight=150" color="#75252a"]As the title subtly implies, Cairo Jazz Club started off as Cairo’s core jazz hub before expanding its showcase to a variety of music genres. CJC’s signature Jazz night plays refuge to genuine music enthusiasts, platforming the best of jazz and world fusion, performed by Egypt’s most sophisticated International and local musicians. Some of our X Sunday regulars; Cocoon, Voice & Bass, Hassan Ramzy and H.O.H. [/cjc_night][cjc_night title="Manic Monday" img="907" embed="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ds4blep9EQE" color="#50223c"]Manic Monday offers cool and current dance beats for our energetic and adventurous music devotees. This night is always trending, always slick and always ready to satisfy. Some of our Manic Monday regulars; Ouzo, Gawdat, Aly Goede and Aguizi & Fahim.[/cjc_night][cjc_night title="Alt Tuesday" img="910" embed="https://soundcloud.com/cairo-jazz-club/mem-machine-eat-man-at-cairo-jazz-club-jan-2017" color="#322e3d"]Alt Tuesday provides originality and uniqueness in the form of live bands, electronic musicians and acoustic artists. If you are looking for musical diversity week after week, this is your night. Some of our Alt Tuesday regulars; Radio Acid, Dokkan, The Meteors Project and Wust El Balad. [/cjc_night][cjc_night title="Spinning Wednesday" img="911" embed="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ds4blep9EQE" color="#971f20"]Home to our famous ‘Boogie Night’, Spinning Wednesday adds a dose of fun and nostalgia to the midweek. This signature party night reminds us that, whatever age we are, it’s always good to let our hair down. Some of our Spinning Wednesday regulars; Ramy DJunkie, Feedo, A.K and Disco Masr.

Boogie Night (Boogie / Disco)                Say Whaat!? (RnB & Hip Hop) Disco 7amra (Arabic Electro Disco)        Old Skool House (90’s House) Dirrrty Pop! (90’s Pop)                             Bigger Better Louder (RnB & Hip Hop) Taxi El Sahra (Arabic Pop)

[/cjc_night][cjc_night title="Thursday Night Live" img="914" color="#e4722c"]Thursday Night Live events kick start every weekend with a lineup of our most vibrant and energetic bands and electronic acts; performing the hits we all love to hear, from fun covers, and rockin’ originals to hearty dancefloor beats. Some of our Thursday Night Live regulars; Massar Egbari, Ritza, Funk Off and Glass Onion. [/cjc_night][cjc_night title="Friday Fever" img="916" color="#414141"]House music with a dynamic twist is on offer every Friday Fever, making CJC a no-brainer weekend dance haven party choice. Leave all inhibitions at the door and come ready to dance. Some of our Friday Fever regulars; Mohasseb, A- Squared, Misty & Hafez and Special K. [/cjc_night][cjc_night title="Saturday L'oriental" img="918" embed="https://soundcloud.com/cairo-jazz-club/asia-madani" color="#5c5237"]Saturday L’oriental musicians add a dash of tradition and a sprinkle of mystery with great musicianship to awaken authentic and contemporary Arabian flare in all of us. Some of our Saturday L'oriental regulars; Basheer, El Dor El Awal, Sorour and Hawas. [/cjc_night][/vc_column][/vc_row]
